article.headline: Florida A&M 93, Md.-Eastern Shore 60
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Leslie Robinson scored 19 points as Florida A&M cruised to a 93-60 victory over Maryland-Eastern Shore on Saturday. FAMU (15-12, 9-5 Mid Eastern Athletic Conference) out-rebounded the Hawks 49-28, and outscored them 44-18 in the paint. Robinson was 7-of-10 from the field, including 5-of-8 from the 3-point line. Rome Sanders scored 18 points, and Brian Green added 14 points and 10 rebounds for the Rattlers. Darius Glover also finished with a double-double, scoring 11 points and pulling down 10 rebounds, and both Greene and Glover added six assists. Ed Tyson scored a game-high 26 points for Md.-Eastern Shore (3-22, 0-13 MEAC), but did not have much help. Aleksandar Popovic was the only other Hawk in double figures with eleven points. The Rattlers used an 11-3 run midway through the first half to take control of the game, and led 42-28 at the break.
